description.plain:
Oakley Neil H T Caesar-Su (born June 4, 1998), professionally known as Central Cee, is an artist hailing from Shepherds Bush, West London and is proving himself to be one of London’s most exciting emerging artists.

Impressing with his short freestyles from as young as 14-years old, Cench originally fell under the trapwave genre through his use of autotune and melodies, as shown on his early 2017 EP 17, and Next Up? freestyle.

It was through the drop of his singles “Day In The Life” and “Molly” in June 2020, as well as his Mad About Bars Freestyle in August 2020, in which Cench “found his voice” – gliding along 808 bass lines, stuttering hats, and slick, cascading flows that add polish to his gritty street-level narration making him one to watch. He garnered major popularity in October 2020 after dropping his single “Loading”  which shot him into the limelight – entering at Number 19 on the UK Top 20 Single Charts.

Central Cee’s full-debut mixtape Wild West was released on March 12 2021. The project contains the aforementioned singles, as well as “Pinging (6 Figures)”, “Commitment Issues”, “6 for 6” and “Fraud”. Posing as a critical and commercial success, it debuted at Number 2 on the UK Album Charts.  He capped off his 2021 by winning the GRM Daily Rated Award for Breakthrough Artist of the Year and Male Artist of the Year.

In February 2022, Cench’s sophomore mixtape 23 was released. The project features his September 2021 PinkPantheress sampled viral single “Obsessed With You”, a track in which entered the UK Top 10 Singles Chart at #4. The mixtape also marked Cench’s very first Number 1 project as it debuted on the UK Official Charts at the very top.

In July 2022, Cench linked up with renowned American director and founder of Lyrical Lemonade, Cole Bennett and dropped the single “Doja”. In the short time of the snippet being released, the single became a viral sensation and Cench’s biggest song to date. In October 2022, Cench dropped the four-track EP No More Leaks as a surprise, being accompanied by the projects leading single “One Up” hours before to battle the plethora of leaks that were happening a week prior.

songs.title: Doja

description.plain:
“Doja” is Central Cee’s first single since the release of his February 2022 mixtape 23 as well as a string of music videos from the mixtape. The track’s beat samples Eve and Gwen Stefani’s classic May 2001 track, “Let Me Blow Ya Mind.”

The rapper first performed the track at Wireless in July 2022, prompting fans to repost the performance on YouTube. Cench also sent flirtatious shots towards American artist Doja Cat, making the meaning of the title clear. On July 15th, 2022, the rapper released a TikTok teaser of the track, announcing the July 21st release date.

Later that day, video director and Lyrical Lemonade founder Cole Bennett, uploaded a TikTok video of the behind the scenes. The director has worked with various of artists such as Juice WRLD, Justin Bieber, Lil Tecca and many more.

songs.title: LET GO

description.plain:
In “LET GO,” Central Cee vents his feelings over a female and reminisces on times they had, causing him to feel depressed and emotional. The track’s beat samples Passenger’s February 2012 single “Let Her Go.”

On December 8, 2022, Central Cee released a TikTok snippet to the public, captioning it “yay or nay.” However, Central Cee removed the snippet few minutes later and revealed that he wouldn’t release it as his girlfriend, Madeline Argy disapproved of it. Central Cee questioned Madeline for her opinions on the snippet, to which she simply responded with:

no. don’t call girls hoes

On December 11, 2022, Madeline posted a TikTok, singing along to the lyrics, to which she approved the song – where she “changed her mind.” Days after Madeline switched thoughts, Central Cee released an unanticipated extract of the music video on Instagram, captioning it “tomorrow.”

description.plain:
On “Obsessed With You”, West London rapper Central Cee samples London singer PinkPantheress‘ viral  TikTok song “Just for me”.

The song was previewed on Central Cee’s TikTok on August 22nd, and became a viral hit, reaching 7 million views and 1.5 million likes in a day. The song was teased further when Cench and PinkPantheress were seen pictured together at a festival. The single was later dropped as a surprise on the 10th of September 2021.

The visuals were captured in a vlog-type style and was released on the 28th of October. The video features social media personality and model Kenza Boutrif, popularly known as 6kenza, who also featured on the “Commitment Issues” official video.

At the end of the video, Cench also teased his upcoming mixtape with the message:

23 coming soon… Still Loading.

songs.title: Commitment Issues

description.plain:

description.plain:
“Eurovision” is the sixth cut from Cench’s sophomore mixtape 23 and recruits a huge  all-star European crossover with 7 featured artists including France’s Freeze Corleone and Ashe 22, Spain’s Beny Jr and Morad, Italy’s Rondodasosa and Baby Gang and the UK’s, Shepherds Bush West London native A2anti. This marks it as two representatives from each country.

Also featuring a huge European producer-crossover with the Cench’s in-house producer, the UK’s Young Chencs, as well as Freeze Corleone’s in-house producer, France’s Flem and Seven 7oo’s in-house producer, Italy’s NKO.

This was first teased on the placeholder tracklist, Cench teased that Track 7 will include five features – which was later changed to Track 6 with 7 features.

Cench has a huge following in all of these European countries, taking Italy, France and Spain by storm as he began to blow up within the UK – previously collaborating with Rondososa on the hit single “MOVIE” in February 2021 and Freeze Corleone on their smash hit single “Polemique” in May 2021.

In February 2022, Cench’s social medias showed him taking flights to Spain, Italy and then France, teasing at this possibility of a music video for this, likely making it the project’s fifth single.

description.plain:
“Retail Therapy” is the second single and fifth track to Shepherds Bush, West London rapper Central Cee’s sophomore mixtape 23 following the viral hit single, September 2021’s “Obsessed With You”. The track was announced alongside with the tape’s announcement on November 25th.

The song was teased as a snippet was used as the backdrop as Cench teamed up with sneaker company Kick Game for a Christmas giveaway to underprivileged kids in London.

Cench highlights his braggadocious character as he speaks on his materialistic nature, the love for women and how his drug dealing past created a successful money-making segue into his life as a rapper.

The song samples “Wildflower”, a single from 1973 by saxophonist Hank Crawford, which samples elements from the 1972 song “Wildflower” by Skylark. It has previously been sampled by artists such as 2Pac and Eminem.
